title.narrative: OP1: EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION (ECE)

description.narrative: By 2021, national and sub-national Government Ministries and other key stakeholders have improved capacity to implement and monitor inclusive, equitable and quality ECE services., which contributes to Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Early Learning, Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Evaluation And Research, Learning Outcomes, Skills Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, national and sub-national Government Ministries and other key stakeholders have improved capacity to implement and monitor inclusive, equitable and quality ECE services.

description.narrative: With UNICEF’s support, more children in remote areas continued to access quality early learning programmes with trained teachers and quality learning materials. Young children and their families nationwide benefitted from additional episodes of educational TV programmes and printed storybooks, which also helped mitigate learning loss from school closures. To enhance the quality of ECE, the revised pre-primary curriculum has been completed for rollout in 2022, and quality standards for pre-school education are under development. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/01/2022
